..TEXT:
Like the heavenly messenger at the walls of Dis (^Inf~.
IX.100-103), this angel, after blessing his flock, also moves away from
those he has helped as quickly as possible, but on this occasion not
from disgust at the place in which he finds himself, but to return to
Ostia for more saved souls.
The souls fling themselves upon the shore (^si gittar~) just as the
damned fling themselves (^gittansi~) upon Charon's boat (^Inf~.
III.116), but with key elements in the scenes significantly reversed,
though both groups are spurred by their desire for justice.
