For the resemblances of the mount of purgatory to Mt. Sinai see
Carol Kaske ("Mount Sinai and Dante's Mount Purgatory," ^Dante Studies~
89 [1971], pp. 1-18.).  For her the mountain is not only its former
self, site of the divine gift of Ten Commandments to Moses, but a place
of Christian pilgrimage under the New Law.
