Virgil's recollection of the difficult journey up through hell
is made to reflect the poet's own formulation in ^Inferno~ I.5 exactly:
^aspra e forte~ (dense and harsh), the adjectives there referring to
the 'dark wood' of the world in which Dante found himself at the outset.
