Satan, with his three heads, had seemed a ^maraviglia~ to the
protagonist in ^Inferno~ XXXIV.37.  In the last canto it was the
miraculous 'resurrection' of the Christlike humble plant (verse 134)
that had seemed a 'wonder' to him.  Now it is ^he~ who causes wonder in
the onlookers, since he is present in the flesh.
