Casella's smile is the first one we have seen since Limbo, when
Virgil smiled to see the poets of antiquity welcome Dante as they
prepared to include him in their noble company (^Inf~. IV.99).  Smiles,
understandably absent from the visages of those in hell, will be more
frequent in purgatory, some dozen of them, and still more so in
paradise (two dozen).
