..REFS:
EN-A20-O2-L111 A20-O2-L111
..TEXT:
Dante's soul, wearied by his bodily weight, remembers his
condition at the beginning of ^Inferno~ I.22: in simile, his mind, in
stress, is like the breath of a man escaping from death by drowning,
^affannata~ (laboring).  If he seems better off now than he was then,
he is still in considerable difficulty.
